(169, 'kumarz', '01/08/2018', '12:17:47', 'page  Delete', '[{"page_id":"82","title":"Vinit Biodata","menu_type":"1","m_id":"71","pg_type":"0","image":"","url_type":"0","content":"<div class=\\"container\\"><div id=\\"mw-content-text\\" lang=\\"en\\" dir=\\"ltr\\" class=\\"mw-content-ltr\\" style=\\"direction: ltr; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\\"><div class=\\"mw-parser-output\\"><p style=\\"margin-top: 0.5em; margin-bottom: 0.5em; line-height: inherit;\\">In&nbsp;<a href=\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Industrial_and_organizational_psychology\\" title=\\"Industrial and organizational psychology\\" style=\\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\">industrial and organizational psychology<\\/a>,&nbsp;<b>biodata<\\/b>&nbsp;is biographical data.<sup id=\\"cite_ref-1\\" class=\\"reference\\" style=\\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\\"><a href=\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Biodata#cite_note-1\\" style=\\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\">[1]<\\/a><\\/sup>&nbsp;Biodata is \\u201c...factual kinds of questions about life and work experiences, as well as items involving opinions, values, beliefs, and attitudes that reflect a historical perspective.\\u201d<sup id=\\"cite_ref-2\\" class=\\"reference\\" style=\\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\\"><a href=\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Biodata#cite_note-2\\" style=\\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\">[2]<\\/a><\\/sup>&nbsp;Since the respondent replies to questions about themselves, there are elements of both biography and autobiography. The basis of biodata\\u2019s predictive abilities is the axiom that past behaviour is the best predictor of future behaviour.<sup id=\\"cite_ref-3\\" class=\\"reference\\" style=\\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\\"><a href=\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Biodata#cite_note-3\\" style=\\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\">[3]<\\/a><\\/sup>&nbsp;Biographical information is not expected to predict all future behaviours but it is useful in personnel selection in that it can give an indication of probable future behaviours based on an individual\\u2019s prior learning history.<sup id=\\"cite_ref-4\\" class=\\"reference\\" style=\\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\\"><a href=\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Biodata#cite_note-4\\" style=\\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\">[4]<\\/a><\\/sup>&nbsp;Biodata instruments (also called&nbsp;<a href=\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Biographical_Information_Blanks\\" title=\\"Biographical Information Blanks\\" style=\\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\">Biographical Information Blanks<\\/a>) have an advantage over personality and interest inventories in that they can capture directly the past behaviour of a person, probably the best predictor of his or her future actions.<sup class=\\"noprint Inline-Template Template-Fact\\" style=\\"line-height: 1; font-size: 11.2px; white-space: nowrap;\\">[<i><a href=\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Wikipedia:Citation_needed\\" title=\\"Wikipedia:Citation needed\\" style=\\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\"><span title=\\"This claim needs references to reliable sources. (June 2018)\\">citation needed<\\/span><\\/a><\\/i>]<\\/sup>&nbsp;These measures deal with facts about the person\\u2019s life, not introspections and subjective judgements.<sup id=\\"cite_ref-5\\" class=\\"reference\\" style=\\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\\"><a href=\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Biodata#cite_note-5\\" style=\\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\">[5]<\\/a><\\/sup>.<\\/p><p style=\\"margin-top: 0.5em; margin-bottom: 0.5em; line-height: inherit;\\">Over the years, personnel selection has relied on standardized psychological tests.<sup id=\\"cite_ref-6\\" class=\\"reference\\" style=\\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\\"><a href=\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Biodata#cite_note-6\\" style=\\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\">[6]<\\/a><\\/sup>&nbsp;The five major categories for these tests are intellectual abilities, spatial and mechanical abilities, perceptual accuracy, motor abilities and personality tests. The mean coefficient for a standardized test of g is 0.51.<sup id=\\"cite_ref-7\\" class=\\"reference\\" style=\\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\\"><a href=\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Biodata#cite_note-7\\" style=\\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\">[7]<\\/a><\\/sup>&nbsp;A review of 58 studies on biodata found coefficients that ranged from 0.32 to 0.46 with a mean validity of 0.35. The mean validity of interviews was found to be 0.19. research has indicated a validity coefficient of 0.29 for unstructured interviews and 0.31 for structured interviews but interview results can be affected by interviewer biases and have been challenged in a number of different court cases.<sup id=\\"cite_ref-8\\" class=\\"reference\\" style=\\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\\"><a href=\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Biodata#cite_note-8\\" style=\\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\">[8]<\\/a><\\/sup><\\/p><p style=\\"margin-top: 0.5em; margin-bottom: 0.5em; line-height: inherit;\\">In summary, biodata has been shown to be a valid and reliable means to predict future performance based on an applicant\\u2019s past performance. A well-constructed biodata instrument is legally defendable and unlike the interview, is not susceptible to error due to rater biases or the halo effect. It has proven its worth in personnel selection as a cost effective tool.<sup id=\\"cite_ref-9\\" class=\\"reference\\" style=\\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\\"><a href=\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Biodata#cite_note-9\\" style=\\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\">[9]<\\/a><\\/sup><\\/p><p style=\\"margin-top: 0.5em; margin-bottom: 0.5em; line-height: inherit;\\">In the&nbsp;<a href=\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/South_Asian\\" class=\\"mw-redirect\\" title=\\"South Asian\\" style=\\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\">South Asian<\\/a>&nbsp;community (<a href=\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Nepal\\" title=\\"Nepal\\" style=\\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\">Nepal<\\/a>,&nbsp;<a href=\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/India\\" title=\\"India\\" style=\\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\">India<\\/a>,&nbsp;<a href=\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Pakistan\\" title=\\"Pakistan\\" style=\\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\">Pakistan<\\/a>,&nbsp;<a href=\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Bangladesh\\" title=\\"Bangladesh\\" style=\\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\">Bangladesh<\\/a>), a biodata is essentially a&nbsp;<a href=\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Resume\\" class=\\"mw-redirect\\" title=\\"Resume\\" style=\\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\">r\\u00e9sum\\u00e9<\\/a>. The purpose is similar to that of a r\\u00e9sum\\u00e9, to eliminate some candidates from the pool of prospective suitors before meeting others. The biodata generally contains the same type of information as a r\\u00e9sum\\u00e9 (i.e. objective, work history, salary information, educational background), but may also include physical attributes, such as height, weight, hair\\/skin\\/eye color, and a photo.<\\/p><h2 style=\\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background: none; margin: 1em 0px 0.25em; overflow: hidden; padding: 0px; border-bottom: 1px solid rgb(162, 169, 177); font-size: 1.5em; font-family: &quot;Linux Libertine&quot;, Georgia, Times, serif; line-height: 1.3;\\"><span class=\\"mw-headline\\" id=\\"References\\">References<\\/span><span class=\\"mw-editsection\\" style=\\"user-select: none; font-size: small; margin-left: 1em; vertical-align: baseline; line-height: 1em; font-family: sans-serif; white-space: nowrap; unicode-bidi: isolate;\\"><span class=\\"mw-editsection-bracket\\" style=\\"margin-right: 0.25em; color: rgb(84, 89, 93);\\">[<\\/span><a href=\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/w\\/index.php?title=Biodata&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\\" title=\\"Edit section: References\\" style=\\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\">edit<\\/a><span c